<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-253  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 253.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CAD-CAM International  Sept 1990 v9 n9 p56(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple 8.24 GC colour card. (Shortlist) (Hardware Review)(evaluation)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer's easy-to-install and -use 1,345-pounds-sterling8.24 GC 24-bit color display card is the most powerful such boardfor the Macintosh II family of microcomputers.andP;  The card featuresan Advanced Micro Devices AMD29000 reduced-instruction-setcomputer (RISC) coprocessor that runs a special version 1.2 ofApple's 32-bit Color Quickdraw up to 30 times faster; it supportsup to 16.7 million simultaneous colors, optional 2Mbytes ofon-board dynamic random-access memory, and the Color Quickdraw andControl Panel device software packages.andP;  The 8.24 GC automaticallyswitches between display modes for a full range of Apple andcompatible displays up to a two-page, 1,152-by-870-pixel array.andO;The 24-bit color capabilities are much more useful for shadedimages for visualization than either Autocad and Microstation,which perform redraws within the software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple 8.24GC (Graphics board).andO;Topic:     EvaluationGraphics Boards-CardsColor.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>